CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1969, pg. 16, reads: "Banquet Committee - Members of the Founder's Day Banquet committee of the alumni chapter of Kappa Alpha Psi are pictured here with principal speaker, Dr. William "Stud" Greene of Washington, D.C. banquet took place at Stouffers Restaurant in Oakland. Seated from left: Ralph Barnett, chairman; Dr. Greene and George Charlton, Polemarch.  Standing from left: William W. Goode, James Greenlee, Robert W. Smith Jr., Arthur Burt and Henry Tate."Seated, first row from left: Bob Smith, Arthur Burt, Rev. James B. Brown, Rev. James B. Cayce, Dr. William "Stud" Green, George Charlton, Ralph Barnett, Lorenzo Hill, Dr. Bailey O. Holland, Dr. Cuthbert, and Robert Williams; second row: three unknown men, John W. Smith Jr., three unknown men, James Greenlee,  unknown man, James Dorsey, Paul Bell, Stanford Evans, Russell Washington, two unknown men, James Laughton, three unknown men, Dr. Leon Ford, unknown, Jonas Hood, Marshall Johnson, Alfred Carl, Sam Lawler II, and James "Buck" Willis; third row: Charles Robinson, unknown man, Andrew Turner, unknown man, Henry Alston, Howard Hailstork, William Goode, Moses Edwards, three unknown men, Fred Gladney, and four unknown man.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Kappa Alpha Psi Fraternity members, gathered behind banquet table in Stouffers Restaurant for Founder's Day banquet
